---
export const prerender = true;

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Product Description — In Parallel"
  description="In Parallel continuously maintains a living execution plan for every execution scope — so plans stay truthful by default and managers get time back to lead."
  navTheme="light"
>
  <section class="bg-white text-ip-navy pt-32 pb-20 md:pt-44 md:pb-32">
    <div class="container-ip max-w-5xl">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-12 md:gap-16">

        <!-- Sidebar navigation -->
        <aside class="md:w-56 shrink-0">
          <nav class="md:sticky md:top-32 flex flex-col gap-3">
            <a
              href="/privacy-policy"
              class="font-display text-sm text-ip-navy/60 border-l-2 border-transparent pl-3 py-1 hover:text-ip-navy transition-colors"
            >
              Privacy Policy
            </a>
            <a
              href="/cookie-policy"
              class="font-display text-sm text-ip-navy/60 border-l-2 border-transparent pl-3 py-1 hover:text-ip-navy transition-colors"
            >
              Cookie Policy
            </a>
            <a
              href="/terms-of-use"
              class="font-display text-sm text-ip-navy/60 border-l-2 border-transparent pl-3 py-1 hover:text-ip-navy transition-colors"
            >
              Terms of Use
            </a>
          </nav>
        </aside>

        <!-- Main content -->
        <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
          <h1 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight text-ip-navy mb-4">
            Product Description
          </h1>
          <p class="text-ip-navy/60 text-sm font-display mb-12">
            Effective November 2025
          </p>

          <div class="space-y-12 text-ip-navy/80 leading-relaxed">

            <!-- Executive Summary -->
            <div>
              <h2 class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl text-ip-navy mb-4">
                Executive Summary
              </h2>
              <p class="mb-4">
                Modern organizations are full of plans, tools, and meetings&mdash;but short on shared execution reality.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-4">
                <li>Goals live in OKR tools.</li>
                <li>Work lives in project systems.</li>
                <li>Decisions are made in meetings.</li>
                <li>Status is reconstructed afterward through decks, spreadsheets, and chat threads.</li>
              </ul>
              <p class="mb-4">
                This creates a persistent coordination tax. Managers spend large portions of their time chasing updates, reconciling versions, and rebuilding shared understanding. Execution does not fail because of missing effort or data&mdash;but because reality changes faster than manual coordination can keep up.
              </p>
              <p class="mb-4">
                <strong class="text-ip-navy">In Parallel removes this tax.</strong>
              </p>
              <p>
                It continuously maintains a living execution plan for every execution scope&mdash;so plans stay truthful by default and managers get time back to lead.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- What the Product Does -->
            <div>
              <h2 class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl text-ip-navy mb-4">
                What the Product Does
              </h2>
              <p class="mb-4">
                In Parallel turns meetings and system updates into a living execution plan that stays current automatically.
              </p>
              <p class="mb-4">It:</p>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 mb-4">
                <li>Captures what happened (decisions, action items, blockers, topics) from your meetings</li>
                <li>Structures captured content into execution plans linked to goals, milestones, and owners</li>
                <li>Identifies what&rsquo;s changed since the last plan was true</li>
                <li>Routes updates to the right people&mdash;across teams, scopes, and rhythms</li>
                <li>Learns over time how your organization actually operates</li>
              </ul>
              <p>
                The result is a continuously updated picture of what&rsquo;s happening, what&rsquo;s shifted, and what needs attention&mdash;without asking anyone to fill in a form or open another dashboard.
              </p>
            </div>

            <!-- Core Capabilities -->
            <div>
              <h2 class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl text-ip-navy mb-4">
                Core Capabilities
              </h2>

              <div class="space-y-6">
                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-ip-navy mb-2">
                    1. Meeting Intelligence
                  </h3>
                  <p>
                    AI-powered capture that joins meetings and extracts structured data: action items, decisions, blockers, discussion topics, and unresolved questions.
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-ip-navy mb-2">
                    2. Living Execution Plans
                  </h3>
                  <p>
                    One persistent view per execution scope. Updated automatically from meetings, integrations, and manual inputs. Linked to goals, timelines, owners, and dependencies.
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-ip-navy mb-2">
                    3. Routing &amp; Escalation Engine
                  </h3>
                  <p>
                    Changes and risks don&rsquo;t stay trapped in meetings. The system routes relevant changes to the right person, the right scope, and the right rhythm.
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-ip-navy mb-2">
                    4. Execution Scopes
                  </h3>
                  <p>
                    Team, Project, Program, Operations, Account, Transformation&mdash;each scope has a plan. Plans connect upward, downward, and sideways.
                  </p>
                </div>

                <div>
                  <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-ip-navy mb-2">
                    5. Organizational Memory
                  </h3>
                  <p>
                    Everything captured is retained, searchable, and structured. The system builds a memory of what happened, what was decided, and what was learned.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- How It Works in Practice -->
            <div>
              <h2 class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl text-ip-navy mb-4">
                How It Works in Practice
              </h2>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                <div>
                  <p>
                    <strong class="text-ip-navy">Before:</strong> A meeting happens. Someone writes notes. Action items may or may not get tracked. The plan is updated manually (if at all).
                  </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <p>
                    <strong class="text-ip-navy">After:</strong> A meeting happens. In Parallel captures, structures, and routes the relevant content. The plan updates itself. Everyone sees the same picture.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Architecture & Security Summary -->
            <div>
              <h2 class="font-display text-xl md:text-2xl text-ip-navy mb-4">
                Architecture &amp; Security Summary
              </h2>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                <li>EU-hosted infrastructure (default)</li>
                <li>ISO 27001 and ISO 42001 certified</li>
                <li>SOC 2 Type II compliant</li>
                <li>GDPR compliant with full DPIA documentation</li>
                <li>SSO/SAML/SCIM, RBAC, full audit logs</li>
                <li>No AI models are trained on customer data</li>
                <li>Data residency options available</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
